Joseph Olaoluwa Benin Electricity Distribution Company has said it has suspended the new service reflective tariff for 14 days. This is in compliance with the order from the Nigerian Electricity Regulatory Commission based on the communique issued after a meeting between the Federal Government and labour unions. The BEDC management in a press release emailed to our correspondent on Monday said it would be complying with the 14-day suspension order which took effect from September 28. Copyright PUNCH.
